  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The SCOPE study is an observational, multicenter, prospective cohort study aimed at
      evaluating a 2-year screening programme for CKD in a population of older patients, aged 75
      years or more, in seven European Countries, in an attempt to investigate whether and to which
      extent currently available screening methods may identify older people at risk of worsening
      kidney function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
